{
  "texts": [
    "Without software export controls and tracking cutting-edge chips, the most capable models proliferate, and government is blind to potentially dangerous clusters of compute.",
    "Dangerous developments might happen in spheres which governments cannot perceive or intervene on.",
    "In these circumstances, the chances for effective regulation of AI are severely diminished.",
    "Hence, the approach has an important role in supporting and enabling other AI regulation efforts.Yet, its long-term potential is limited.",
    "So far, compute has been getting cheaper along a roughly exponential path [24]."
  ]
}